# 📜 Code of Conduct

## Introduction
Welcome to the **Smart Tennis Racket** project! We value collaboration, creativity, and mutual respect within our community. This Code of Conduct outlines the expected behaviors and responsibilities for all contributors to ensure a **positive, inclusive, and productive environment**.

---

## 📌 Our Pledge
We, as contributors and maintainers, pledge to create an open and welcoming environment for everyone, regardless of:

- Age
- Gender identity and expression
- Sexual orientation
- Disability
- Ethnicity
- Level of experience
- Nationality
- Personal appearance
- Race
- Religion (or lack thereof)
- Socioeconomic status

We are committed to fostering a **safe space for learning, sharing, and innovation**.

---

## ✅ Expected Behavior
All contributors are expected to:

- Be **kind** and **respectful** to others.
- Offer **constructive feedback** and be **open to feedback** from others.
- Assume **good intentions** and engage in discussions with **curiosity**.
- **Credit contributors** for their work.
- Keep discussions **relevant to the project**.
- Follow **ethical standards**, including proper attribution for external code or content.

---

## ❌ Unacceptable Behavior
We will not tolerate:

- Harassment, abuse, insults, or discriminatory remarks.
- Trolling, inflammatory or off-topic comments.
- Intimidation, personal attacks, or political/religious arguments.
- Publishing private information (e.g., personal phone numbers, addresses).
- Plagiarism or any unethical copying of code/content.

---

## ⚠️ Reporting Violations
If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior, please report it to:

**Primary Contact:** Aahan Prajapati  
**Email:** aahanprajapati@gmail.com

All reports will be handled with **strict confidentiality**. We will investigate all complaints and respond appropriately.

---

## 🌍 Scope
This Code of Conduct applies to:

- All project spaces (GitHub issues, pull requests, discussions).
- Private or public communications related to the project.
- Any official events or collaborations under the project’s banner.

---

## 🛠️ Enforcement
Project maintainers are responsible for enforcing this Code of Conduct. Actions for confirmed violations may include:

- **Warning** the offender.
- **Temporary or permanent banning** from the project.
- **Removing inappropriate content.**

Decisions will be made at the discretion of maintainers, with fairness and impartiality.

---

## 🙏 Attribution
This Code of Conduct is adapted from the [Contributor Covenant v2.1](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct/).

